Date: 11 Oct 2000 05:46:12 -0700 (PDT)
From: Shamsudeen Fagbo <oloungbo@yahoo.com>
Source: Arab News, filed 11 Oct 2000 [edited

Rift Valley Fever: Update as of 11 Oct 2000
--------------------------------------------------------------
RIYADH- Crown Prince Abdullah, Deputy Premier And Commander of the National
Guard, yesterday ordered the deployment of a full-fledged National Guard
medical team in Jizan to support the ongoing campaign against Rift Valley
fever, which has killed 66 people and infected 335.
Fahd Abdul Jabbar, Executive Director For Health Affairs at the National
Guard, said the team would include 18 doctors and paramedics and would be
provided with all medical requirements to support the existing medical
teams in the region. The National Guard team will include 3 specialists, 4
doctors and 7 nurses.
The Health Ministry said 2 more people died in Jizan of Rift Valley fever
during the past 24 hours, adding that 19 new cases - 13 in Jizan and 6 in
Asir- of Rift Valley fever infection were reported yesterday.
--
Dr Shamsudeen Fagbo
<oloungbo@yahoo.com>
